 the trading day, I agree to buy futures from you at the end of the day, fo=
r whatever the closing (settlement) price happens to be (plus or minus a fe=
w pennies of premium or discount). We agree on a quantity but not a price; =
we just take whatever the closing price is as the price for our trade.</p><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You might be doing this because you are a price=
-insensitive natural seller. I, on the other hand, might be an arbitrageur =
or market maker or prop trader; I might not want to end up owning all those=
 futures. I will hedge my transaction: I=E2=80=99ll buy 100 contracts from =
you via TAS, and then sell 100 contracts in the market =E2=80=94=C2=A0at ac=
tual prices =E2=80=94=C2=A0to end up flat. I might try to do this hedging s=
ometime near the close of trading that day, so that my selling prices will =
roughly match the settlement price at which I am buying.</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin: 16px 0;">If I do a lot of selling=C2=A0<em>right at the close</em>, th=
at will have a tendency to drive down the closing price. If there are no ot=
her big=C2=A0<em>buyers=C2=A0</em>right at the close, this can be very lucr=
ative for me. For instance if the price is $20, half an hour before the clo=
se, and I start selling a bunch and the price drops to $10, and if I sell s=
ome more and it drops to $0, and I sell even more and it drops to negative =
$10, and so forth, I might end up selling my contracts at an average price =
of, say, negative $10, and then I buy from you at the settlement price of, =
say, negative $37.63, which was the actual closing price of West Texas Inte=
rmediate crude futures on April 20, 2020. So I make $27.63 per barrel.=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A point that I often make is that it is=
 very hard, in this scenario, to distinguish proper=C2=A0=E2=80=9Chedging=
=E2=80=9D (I am long TAS, so I hedge by selling futures)=C2=A0from improper=
 =E2=80=9Cmanipulation=E2=80=9D (I am long TAS, so I push down the settleme=
nt price by selling futures). Or rather, two related points that I often ma=
ke are:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margi=
n: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It is hard to distinguish =
